acceleration /ækˌsɛləˈreɪʃən/

N-UNCOUNT The acceleration of a process or change is the fact that it is getting faster and faster. 增速 

例： He has also called for an acceleration of political reforms. 他也已呼吁加速政治改革。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Acceleration is the rate at which a car or other vehicle can increase its speed, often seen in terms of the time that it takes to reach a particular speed. 加速幅度 

例： Acceleration to 60 mph takes a mere 5.7 seconds. 加速到每小时60英里仅用5.7秒。 

3. N-UNCOUNT Acceleration is the rate at which the speed of an object increases. 加速度 [技术]

</div>

